WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:01:03.855 --> 00:01:05.941
Glad news. Lord Ormund!

3
00:01:07.150 --> 00:01:09.152
The war is ended.
your allies have scattered.

4
00:01:09.194 --> 00:01:10.862
and your nephews fled.

5
00:01:10.904 --> 00:01:13.615
There is a new queen and
she sits her father's throne.

6
00:01:15.450 --> 00:01:17.035
We heard rumor of this.

7
00:01:18.287 --> 00:01:21.081
Though on the road.
rumors swarm like flies.

8
00:01:21.123 --> 00:01:22.749
Well. the queen. in her wisdom.
offered you clemency.

9
00:01:22.791 --> 00:01:24.209
and your army with you.

10
00:01:25.085 --> 00:01:27.379
Only bend the knee
and swear your allegiance.

11
00:01:27.421 --> 00:01:32.175
and you may return to Oldtown
and live your lives in... peace.

12
00:01:32.217 --> 00:01:34.344
Have you any proof of your claim?

13
00:01:34.386 --> 00:01:36.555
Or am I to trust
in the reliability

14
00:01:36.597 --> 00:01:39.016
and rectitude
of the Rogue Prince?

15
00:01:39.057 --> 00:01:42.561
Trust me or don't. You will encounter
the truth soon enough.

16
00:01:42.603 --> 00:01:44.896
Your uncle Otto encountered it
very recently...

17
00:01:45.772 --> 00:01:47.774
and the Hightower guard
soon after him.

18
00:01:50.402 --> 00:01:52.529
And if I am inclined to fight?

19
00:01:52.571 --> 00:01:54.197
That seems obvious enough.

20
00:01:54.239 --> 00:01:56.617
No need to sully the pleasantness
of this meeting.

21
00:02:00.078 --> 00:02:03.457
Though I must say.
I think Ulf there

22
00:02:03.498 --> 00:02:06.543
would very much enjoy settling into
your chambers in the High Tower.

23
00:02:06.585 --> 00:02:09.588
Would you like to be
Lord of Oldtown. Ulf?

24
00:02:18.263 --> 00:02:19.806
I am left no choice.

25
00:02:21.266 --> 00:02:23.185
For myself. I would resist.

26
00:02:24.353 --> 00:02:26.688
But I have many other
lives to consider.

27
00:02:27.939 --> 00:02:29.983
And so. in the interest
of peace...

28
00:02:32.110 --> 00:02:33.111
I will submit.

29
00:02:33.153 --> 00:02:34.321
Delightful.

30
00:02:46.792 --> 00:02:49.169
I. Ormund Hightower.

31
00:02:49.211 --> 00:02:50.754
promise to be faithful

32
00:02:50.796 --> 00:02:53.423
to Rhaenyra Targaryen.
the queen.

33
00:02:53.465 --> 00:02:55.592
I pledge my fealty to her.

34
00:02:55.634 --> 00:02:57.427
You have chosen wisely.

35
00:02:57.469 --> 00:02:59.346
if reluctantly.
Lord Ormund.

36
00:02:59.388 --> 00:03:01.139
Turn around now
and lead your army home.

37
00:03:01.181 --> 00:03:02.683
and you will be spared.

38
00:03:15.153 --> 00:03:16.988
Our campaign has ended.

39
00:03:18.407 --> 00:03:20.367
We take the Roseroad homeward.

40
00:03:21.702 --> 00:03:22.703
Ah!

41
00:03:25.205 --> 00:03:27.249
I almost forgot.

42
00:03:28.917 --> 00:03:30.043
Your ward...

43
00:03:31.211 --> 00:03:33.046
Daeron Targaryen.

44
00:03:33.088 --> 00:03:34.381
He'll be coming with me.

45
00:03:38.343 --> 00:03:39.970
You would take him hostage?

46
00:03:40.011 --> 00:03:41.638
It would be rather
an oversight to allow

47
00:03:41.680 --> 00:03:43.806
one of Prince Aegon's heirs
to go prancing about the Reach

48
00:03:43.807 --> 00:03:45.641
with his dragon. no less.

49
00:03:45.642 --> 00:03:49.187
We will treat him kindly.
as we would any son of Viserys.

50
00:03:50.105 --> 00:03:51.857
As long as you behave yourself.

51
00:04:24.723 --> 00:04:26.391
Be brave. young prince.

52
00:04:43.241 --> 00:04:44.409
Well met. nephew.

53
00:04:45.994 --> 00:04:47.078
Go home.

54
00:06:50.243 --> 00:06:52.704
The air is thick with ghosts.

55
00:06:59.044 --> 00:07:00.337
Not unhappy ones.

56
00:07:00.378 --> 00:07:02.589
I see myself
as a child coming to...

57
00:07:04.633 --> 00:07:06.217
play him a tune
I had learned.

58
00:07:09.429 --> 00:07:10.805
He was strong then.

59
00:07:12.265 --> 00:07:14.225
And my mother.

60
00:07:20.899 --> 00:07:23.068
Lord Ormund surrendered.

61
00:07:24.069 --> 00:07:25.987
We have your little prince.

62
00:07:26.738 --> 00:07:28.949
Though I still say we should
have incinerated them all.

63
00:07:32.118 --> 00:07:34.746
I must justify
my father's faith in me.

64
00:07:37.165 --> 00:07:39.459
Rule as he would have wished.

65
00:07:43.421 --> 00:07:45.006
At any rate. we must begin.

66
00:07:52.180 --> 00:07:55.642
The sooner I'm formally crowned.
the better.

67
00:07:55.684 --> 00:07:58.812
Though the preparations
are no small undertaking.

68
00:07:58.853 --> 00:08:01.606
To house and feed all those
who must attend. to...

69
00:08:02.941 --> 00:08:05.694
organize tourneys.
The grand procession.

70
00:08:07.028 --> 00:08:08.029
Ah.

71
00:08:09.781 --> 00:08:12.492
Daeron Targaryen. Your Grace.

72
00:08:17.664 --> 00:08:19.499
We've not met.

73
00:08:19.541 --> 00:08:22.877
I'm your half-sister
and our father's chosen heir.

74
00:08:24.462 --> 00:08:27.424
You've flown in service
of your brother. the usurper.

75
00:08:27.465 --> 00:08:28.633
What have you to say?

76
00:08:31.136 --> 00:08:33.262
Open your mouth
and speak to your queen.

77
00:08:33.263 --> 00:08:36.098
You are a prisoner
in this house.

78
00:08:36.099 --> 00:08:39.936
Your treatment will depend on
your conduct and your pliancy.

79
00:08:39.978 --> 00:08:40.979
Look at me.

80
00:08:41.813 --> 00:08:44.274
I wish to know
what Ormund knew

81
00:08:44.315 --> 00:08:46.317
of the conspiracy
to deny me my throne.

82
00:08:48.361 --> 00:08:50.989
What of Aemond. then?
Or Aegon?

83
00:08:52.323 --> 00:08:54.325
What do you know
of their movements?

84
00:08:57.579 --> 00:08:59.622
Oh. as you wish.

85
00:08:59.664 --> 00:09:00.874
Confine him to a chamber.

86
00:09:02.333 --> 00:09:03.668
Coming down!

87
00:09:08.757 --> 00:09:11.968
He's younger than I imagined.

88
00:09:12.010 --> 00:09:14.304
He's a claimant to the throne.

89
00:09:14.345 --> 00:09:16.056
You're going to
have to kill him.

90
00:09:16.097 --> 00:09:17.891
...was Tyland Lannister.

91
00:09:17.932 --> 00:09:19.225
He did not confide in me.

92
00:09:19.267 --> 00:09:21.478
I know only that he spoke
of dividing the gold

93
00:09:21.519 --> 00:09:23.521
and sending it out of the city
for safekeeping.

94
00:09:23.563 --> 00:09:25.315
- What gold?
- It appears. Your Grace.

95
00:09:25.356 --> 00:09:26.816
the crown's wealth
has been taken.

96
00:09:26.858 --> 00:09:29.652
- Taken?
- Your treasury is depleted.

97
00:09:29.694 --> 00:09:32.321
There is enough to see your
court through a week or two.

98
00:09:32.322 --> 00:09:34.657
A little longer if you bring back the gold
from Dragonstone.

99
00:09:34.699 --> 00:09:37.535
But to administer
all of the Seven Kingdoms...

100
00:09:37.577 --> 00:09:40.246
No.
What of my coronation?

101
00:09:40.288 --> 00:09:41.915
Oh. you must know something.

102
00:09:41.956 --> 00:09:43.500
They told me little.

103
00:09:43.541 --> 00:09:45.335
Perhaps because
they trusted me little.

104
00:09:45.376 --> 00:09:47.003
Do you trust his word.
Lord Corlys?

105
00:09:47.045 --> 00:09:49.714
I do not believe he knows
where the gold is.

106
00:09:49.756 --> 00:09:51.841
And I fancy I can sniff a lie.

107
00:09:51.883 --> 00:09:53.259
No one asked you.

108
00:09:54.844 --> 00:09:59.515
It is the duty of
my Mistress of Whisperers to advise me.

109
00:09:59.516 --> 00:10:01.893
After the Gullet. we must
presume Ser Tyland dead.

110
00:10:03.228 --> 00:10:04.729
But he must have told someone.

111
00:10:04.771 --> 00:10:06.731
If he did.
it would have been Lord Jasper.

112
00:10:08.233 --> 00:10:09.984
"Ironrod."

113
00:10:11.277 --> 00:10:12.445
Oh. dear.

114
00:10:15.490 --> 00:10:17.742
Our circumstances are...

115
00:10:20.120 --> 00:10:21.454
unfortunate.

116
00:10:21.496 --> 00:10:23.581
But this remains.
I must have a coronation.

117
00:10:24.791 --> 00:10:26.292
Aegon's was done in haste.

118
00:10:27.585 --> 00:10:29.963
Mine must be proper
and leave the realm in no doubt

119
00:10:30.004 --> 00:10:31.756
as to who now rules them.

120
00:10:31.798 --> 00:10:34.968
It. uh. it seems to me.
my queen.

121
00:10:35.009 --> 00:10:38.888
that to go to such expense
while your people still suffer

122
00:10:38.930 --> 00:10:42.392
might set a bitter taste
in their mouths.

123
00:10:42.433 --> 00:10:45.145
It is not mere vanity.
It is a matter of legitimacy.

124
00:10:45.186 --> 00:10:46.729
The Triarchy navy is finished.

125
00:10:46.771 --> 00:10:49.399
but the pirates who survived
have come ashore.

126
00:10:49.440 --> 00:10:51.234
They are sacking villages.

127
00:10:51.276 --> 00:10:54.237
They are taking women
and demanding ransoms none can pay.

128
00:10:54.279 --> 00:10:56.739
And difficulties
abound in the city. Your Grace.

129
00:10:56.781 --> 00:10:58.741
It seems the granaries
are near empty.

130
00:10:58.783 --> 00:11:00.326
The fields lie fallow

131
00:11:00.368 --> 00:11:02.245
and the planting season
is moons away.

132
00:11:02.287 --> 00:11:03.913
If we could find some trade...

133
00:11:03.955 --> 00:11:06.624
It will take time for the routes
to be reestablished.

134
00:11:07.625 --> 00:11:09.252
And we have
not enough ships now

135
00:11:09.294 --> 00:11:11.420
to ensure the safety of goods
on the high sea.

136
00:11:11.421 --> 00:11:13.423
Well. in the meantime.
we must find grain for bread

137
00:11:13.464 --> 00:11:15.008
or have the people
go hungry again.

138
00:11:15.049 --> 00:11:16.968
It is a never-ending inconvenience.

139
00:11:17.010 --> 00:11:19.596
this insistence
of the people being fed.

140
00:11:19.637 --> 00:11:22.140
And yet. a hungry population
is a dangerous one.

141
00:11:22.182 --> 00:11:24.100
as the queen and I well know.

142
00:11:24.142 --> 00:11:27.312
How much time will
we squander here on trifles?

143
00:11:27.353 --> 00:11:28.521
The war is won.

144
00:11:28.563 --> 00:11:30.857
Send another raven
to Casterly Rock.

145
00:11:30.899 --> 00:11:33.610
If Tyland secreted gold there.

146
00:11:33.651 --> 00:11:35.445
we will have an answer
from Lady Johanna.

147
00:11:35.486 --> 00:11:37.989
Send to all the great houses.

148
00:11:38.031 --> 00:11:39.324
In fact. tell them...

149
00:11:40.325 --> 00:11:42.619
their queen demands tribute.

150
00:11:42.660 --> 00:11:44.786
Remind them who now
commands the realm.

151
00:11:44.787 --> 00:11:47.874
Will you not bring
your small council here from Dragonstone?

152
00:11:49.000 --> 00:11:50.543
There is much to take in hand.

153
00:11:50.585 --> 00:11:54.297
They betrayed me in their silence.
if not in deed.

154
00:11:54.339 --> 00:11:55.548
I have done with them.

155
00:11:57.675 --> 00:11:59.385
Where is Aemond?

156
00:11:59.427 --> 00:12:02.138
He burned Daemon's garrison
at Harrenhal

157
00:12:02.180 --> 00:12:04.224
and slew the castellan
and his sons.

158
00:12:05.558 --> 00:12:07.685
And then. he disappeared.

159
00:12:10.521 --> 00:12:13.274
It is days now
since Vhagar was last seen.

160
00:12:14.692 --> 00:12:17.820
There was a woman there.
a maester of sorts.

161
00:12:17.862 --> 00:12:19.530
I have not heard tell of her.

162
00:12:19.572 --> 00:12:21.658
Aemond would not
dare challenge you here.

163
00:12:21.699 --> 00:12:24.202
No.
But I want him found.

164
00:12:24.244 --> 00:12:25.870
And Sheepstealer as well.

165
00:12:26.913 --> 00:12:30.041
They are the dangers.
Let Baela fly as a scout.

166
00:12:30.083 --> 00:12:33.586
Start at Harrenhal and report
when there are sightings.

167
00:12:33.628 --> 00:12:35.838
I will. in addition.
offer a bounty

168
00:12:35.880 --> 00:12:37.757
for the capture of their riders.

169
00:12:37.799 --> 00:12:39.968
We don't have a bounty.
it seems.

170
00:12:41.135 --> 00:12:42.428
We will find one.

171
00:12:42.470 --> 00:12:44.097
Ah. better yet.

172
00:12:44.138 --> 00:12:47.558
to the slayer of Aemond One-Eye.
I will grant Harrenhal itself.

173
00:12:47.600 --> 00:12:50.144
I have no need of it now.
All the Riverlands are mine.

174
00:12:52.480 --> 00:12:55.566
Ah. yes. Aegon hanged
all the rat catchers.

175
00:12:58.403 --> 00:13:00.697
As honored as I am
to act as your protector.

176
00:13:00.738 --> 00:13:03.366
my place is with my men
in the city.

177
00:13:03.408 --> 00:13:06.369
I would counsel you to appoint
a Queensguard as a matter of urgency.

178
00:13:06.411 --> 00:13:08.204
Daemon will be useful
in identifying candidates.

179
00:13:08.246 --> 00:13:10.707
- We'll put the matter to him.
- My queen. a moment.

180
00:13:10.748 --> 00:13:13.626
It seems rats have eaten through
a large store of candles.

181
00:13:13.668 --> 00:13:15.962
Tallow is short. we... we must
requisition a new supply

182
00:13:16.004 --> 00:13:17.880
or sit in darkness.

183
00:13:17.922 --> 00:13:20.425
- Then requisition it.
- Of course. There is none yet

184
00:13:20.466 --> 00:13:21.968
- to control the royal purse.
- Begging your pardon. good ser.

185
00:13:22.010 --> 00:13:23.552
In the matter
of the bed chamber.

186
00:13:23.553 --> 00:13:25.554
- uh. I didn't know who to ask.
- It's a matter for later.

187
00:13:25.555 --> 00:13:27.473
Hightower bannerman
control the Arbor.

188
00:13:27.515 --> 00:13:29.892
- My lady. the price of good wine...
- Move back!

189
00:13:29.934 --> 00:13:31.978
...has tripled. if not more.

190
00:13:32.020 --> 00:13:33.438
Enough. enough!

191
00:13:34.814 --> 00:13:36.649
There is time aplenty
in the coming days

192
00:13:36.691 --> 00:13:37.984
to discuss the royal tipple.

193
00:13:38.943 --> 00:13:40.153
Where is my gold?

194
00:13:42.113 --> 00:13:45.074
- Your gold?
- The crown's gold. the treasury.

195
00:13:45.116 --> 00:13:47.743
- Oh. you cannot claim ignorance.
- I'm of no help to you.

196
00:13:47.744 --> 00:13:49.620
It was the Master of Coin
who removed it.

197
00:13:49.662 --> 00:13:51.414
And the queen
knew nothing of it?

198
00:13:51.456 --> 00:13:53.249
They hated me from the start.

199
00:13:53.291 --> 00:13:55.293
Resented my influence.
my mere presence.

200
00:13:55.335 --> 00:13:56.753
My own father
kept their plot from me.

201
00:13:56.794 --> 00:13:58.087
Is that so?

202
00:13:58.129 --> 00:13:59.589
I would refer you
to the man himself.

203
00:13:59.630 --> 00:14:01.466
but you slew him
without ceremony.

204
00:14:02.342 --> 00:14:03.968
Did it make you feel better?

205
00:14:04.969 --> 00:14:06.721
Uh. about losing Jace?

206
00:14:10.558 --> 00:14:13.311
I would rather have slain Aegon
as your mother and I had agreed.

207
00:14:14.729 --> 00:14:17.273
But here we are.
He is gone.

208
00:14:17.315 --> 00:14:19.317
And I cannot believe
you had no hand in that either.

209
00:14:19.359 --> 00:14:20.942
He did that to himself.

210
00:14:20.943 --> 00:14:22.611
Aegon was fled when
I returned from Dragonstone.

211
00:14:22.612 --> 00:14:24.447
Has Orwyle not given you
his account?

212
00:14:24.489 --> 00:14:26.282
His account. or yours?

213
00:14:26.324 --> 00:14:28.117
Do not treat me as a fool.

214
00:14:28.159 --> 00:14:29.619
If you require me to foresee

215
00:14:29.660 --> 00:14:31.788
every duplicitous scheme
devised by Larys Strong.

216
00:14:31.829 --> 00:14:33.623
I confess I cannot help
but fall short.

217
00:14:33.664 --> 00:14:34.957
Where is Vhagar?

218
00:14:34.999 --> 00:14:37.627
- Who rides Sheepstealer?
- I do not know!

219
00:14:37.668 --> 00:14:40.546
Is Aemond not flown away
as I promised?

220
00:14:40.588 --> 00:14:42.673
Did the guards on the parapets
not suffer you to pass?

221
00:14:42.715 --> 00:14:45.134
I have done all I could.

222
00:14:45.176 --> 00:14:47.512
Will you blame me only
for what men have done?

223
00:14:47.553 --> 00:14:49.347
You promised we could go.

224
00:14:49.389 --> 00:14:52.058
We told the guards.
We ran.

225
00:14:56.938 --> 00:14:58.689
No one knows
what he looks like.

226
00:15:00.024 --> 00:15:01.651
Aegon.

227
00:15:01.692 --> 00:15:03.653
He's scarred and burned.

228
00:15:03.694 --> 00:15:05.947
His dragon is dead.
Declare him dead as well.

229
00:15:07.323 --> 00:15:09.951
He cannot fight. and if Larys
tries to raise him up...

230
00:15:10.868 --> 00:15:13.704
you can dismiss him
as an impostor.

231
00:15:18.960 --> 00:15:21.546
You argue still for his life?

232
00:15:24.799 --> 00:15:26.300
You killed my father.

233
00:15:44.902 --> 00:15:45.903
When...

234
00:15:47.113 --> 00:15:49.782
Aemond has been found...

235
00:15:51.492 --> 00:15:53.995
and the challenge to me...

236
00:15:55.163 --> 00:15:57.874
removed. you will go free.

237
00:15:57.915 --> 00:16:00.793
But until then. I cannot be seen
to favor Hightowers.

238
00:16:01.752 --> 00:16:03.629
I don't want to stay
in this room.

239
00:16:03.671 --> 00:16:05.256
I will not treat you unkindly.

240
00:16:06.507 --> 00:16:09.927
You will be fed
and clothed and...

241
00:16:11.095 --> 00:16:13.890
and have a maid
to suit your needs.

242
00:16:13.931 --> 00:16:15.725
You may walk under guard
in the Godswood...

243
00:16:15.766 --> 00:16:17.393
- Uh...
- ...and I will have Jaehaera brought to you

244
00:16:17.435 --> 00:16:18.728
for an hour
every few days or so.

245
00:16:18.769 --> 00:16:20.730
You cannot mean this.
Rhaenyra. please.

246
00:16:20.771 --> 00:16:22.523
None of this pleases me.

247
00:16:25.610 --> 00:16:28.029
So my position is such
that I must hope...

248
00:16:28.988 --> 00:16:30.907
for the capture
and death of my son.

249
00:16:35.119 --> 00:16:36.704
I can only imagine.

250
00:16:38.164 --> 00:16:40.791
I want it proclaimed that
we discovered Aegon here. dead.

251
00:16:42.210 --> 00:16:44.128
- A shrewd gambit. Your Grace.
- And let Joffrey

252
00:16:44.170 --> 00:16:45.671
be brought back from the Vale.

253
00:16:45.713 --> 00:16:48.049
He is next in line.
He must now be raised as my heir.

254
00:16:53.846 --> 00:16:57.099
I know much about this place.
but never seen it before today.

255
00:16:57.141 --> 00:16:58.684
Is it as you imagined?

256
00:16:58.726 --> 00:17:01.437
It is both larger
and smaller.

257
00:17:01.479 --> 00:17:02.855
- Hm.
- I will guess that Alicent

258
00:17:02.897 --> 00:17:04.273
had no confidence to give you

259
00:17:04.315 --> 00:17:05.942
as to the whereabouts
of the gold.

260
00:17:05.983 --> 00:17:07.151
She did not.

261
00:17:07.193 --> 00:17:08.486
And you trust her yet?

262
00:17:11.906 --> 00:17:13.824
She is a Hightower.

263
00:17:13.866 --> 00:17:15.368
True.

264
00:17:15.409 --> 00:17:17.619
But would I not be simple
to think that in a house

265
00:17:17.620 --> 00:17:19.997
as big as this one.
there were only one rat?

266
00:17:22.500 --> 00:17:24.293
I am much troubled
about her son Daeron.

267
00:17:24.335 --> 00:17:26.295
- whom we now hold captive.
- Does she know?

268
00:17:26.337 --> 00:17:29.173
By rights. I should have
his head for a traitor.

269
00:17:29.215 --> 00:17:32.468
He is an heir to Aegon
and a threat to you.

270
00:17:32.510 --> 00:17:34.720
Yet he is also my half-brother
and has not committed the crimes

271
00:17:34.762 --> 00:17:36.681
that Aegon and Aemond have.
and yet is...

272
00:17:54.240 --> 00:17:57.660
Why should I not kill him?
Why should I not...

273
00:17:57.702 --> 00:17:59.912
strike him as my own sons
were stricken?

274
00:18:00.955 --> 00:18:02.456
There is none to stop you.

275
00:18:03.708 --> 00:18:05.042
There are mountains
to be dealt with.

276
00:18:05.084 --> 00:18:06.669
and I have none yet
to trust with them.

277
00:18:06.711 --> 00:18:08.879
My lady-in-waiting. Elinda?

278
00:18:08.921 --> 00:18:10.506
Elinda Massey
is now in the city.

279
00:18:10.548 --> 00:18:13.009
- having served us well there.
- Better send to her.

280
00:18:13.050 --> 00:18:14.844
And Mysaria.

281
00:18:14.885 --> 00:18:16.929
let the staff be questioned.

282
00:18:18.055 --> 00:18:19.557
Quietly. as only you can.

283
00:18:20.725 --> 00:18:22.268
Those who cleave
to the Hightowers

284
00:18:22.310 --> 00:18:23.561
must be replaced.

285
00:18:25.896 --> 00:18:27.481
Immediately. Your Grace.

286
00:18:29.066 --> 00:18:30.234
Good morrow. Your Grace.

287
00:18:33.904 --> 00:18:36.073
A blessing in the name
of the Seven Who Are One.

288
00:18:40.745 --> 00:18:43.748
I thank you
for your swift attendance here.

289
00:18:43.789 --> 00:18:46.042
Uh. much has changed
in the last few days.

290
00:18:46.083 --> 00:18:48.336
These are turbulent times.

291
00:18:49.670 --> 00:18:51.380
I must for the time being

292
00:18:51.422 --> 00:18:53.299
forego a right
and proper coronation.

293
00:18:53.341 --> 00:18:55.760
but I still wish at least
to be anointed.

294
00:18:55.801 --> 00:18:58.262
by you. in full sight
of the people.

295
00:19:00.473 --> 00:19:02.975
Alas. that it cannot be done.

296
00:19:04.935 --> 00:19:06.520
For what reason?

297
00:19:08.356 --> 00:19:10.983
Some months ago
I anointed your brother Aegon...

298
00:19:13.027 --> 00:19:15.946
and declared him
the rightful king

299
00:19:15.988 --> 00:19:17.448
before gods and men.

300
00:19:17.490 --> 00:19:20.284
Yes. Aegon is dead.
and I now sit the throne.

301
00:19:25.122 --> 00:19:26.457
So you now say.

302
00:19:27.458 --> 00:19:29.460
Is it your contention
that I am a liar?

303
00:19:31.003 --> 00:19:32.713
We have not seen his remains.

304
00:19:35.007 --> 00:19:37.968
Nor have the Silent Sisters
been summoned to tend to them.

305
00:19:40.971 --> 00:19:42.014
You understand...

306
00:19:43.140 --> 00:19:46.936
that if there has been
some kind of error.

307
00:19:46.977 --> 00:19:49.021
Oh. there has been no error.

308
00:19:49.063 --> 00:19:51.440
I am my father's heir.

309
00:19:51.482 --> 00:19:53.150
And the gods themselves

310
00:19:53.192 --> 00:19:54.944
decree that I must rule
the Seven Kingdoms.

311
00:19:54.985 --> 00:19:57.154
Have they not raised me up

312
00:19:57.196 --> 00:19:59.115
and cast the usurper into ruin?

313
00:19:59.156 --> 00:20:00.616
That has happened.
It is true.

314
00:20:00.658 --> 00:20:02.326
How has it happened
if they did not will it?

315
00:20:05.162 --> 00:20:08.541
A dragon appeared to me
in my greatest need.

316
00:20:08.582 --> 00:20:11.335
My gods do not deal in dragons.

317
00:20:12.503 --> 00:20:14.964
They are a profane magic

318
00:20:15.005 --> 00:20:17.299
created in darkness and pride

319
00:20:17.341 --> 00:20:19.927
and lust for power.
for impunity.

320
00:20:21.011 --> 00:20:24.598
They destroy.
but they do not create.

321
00:20:25.349 --> 00:20:27.351
There is no good
that can come of them.

322
00:20:34.191 --> 00:20:36.527
You have made your position
exceedingly clear.

323
00:20:38.696 --> 00:20:40.489
With respect. I advise you.

324
00:20:40.531 --> 00:20:42.700
do not make an enemy
of the Faith.

325
00:20:43.951 --> 00:20:47.371
It exhorts and comforts
and binds together your people.

326
00:20:48.706 --> 00:20:50.541
Underestimate it at your peril.

327
00:20:52.793 --> 00:20:54.253
I must confess to you now

328
00:20:54.295 --> 00:20:56.422
a thing you may have
guessed before.

329
00:20:58.549 --> 00:21:00.718
Alyn of Hull and his brother
Addam are my sons.

330
00:21:02.011 --> 00:21:04.221
They are born of a woman.
a shipwright

331
00:21:04.263 --> 00:21:06.265
I met on my earlier travels.

332
00:21:07.808 --> 00:21:09.477
I did not claim them as mine.

333
00:21:11.145 --> 00:21:12.313
I was ashamed.

334
00:21:13.355 --> 00:21:16.275
And I dreaded
grieving Rhaenys. my wife.

335
00:21:16.317 --> 00:21:17.902
And I am grateful

336
00:21:17.943 --> 00:21:20.821
she showed me grace
before she died.

337
00:21:23.741 --> 00:21:25.576
I did not guess.

338
00:21:26.911 --> 00:21:31.248
Though I believe
I see it now.

339
00:21:33.584 --> 00:21:35.710
You need fear
no reproach from me.

340
00:21:35.711 --> 00:21:39.465
It is many a lord who has mixed
noble and common blood.

341
00:21:39.507 --> 00:21:42.802
Their sons
are no less stout of heart.

342
00:21:46.096 --> 00:21:48.098
Each has shown himself
worthy of more

343
00:21:48.140 --> 00:21:49.558
than was given him
before now.

344
00:21:49.600 --> 00:21:52.770
Indeed. we owe Alyn
a great debt

345
00:21:52.812 --> 00:21:55.439
for his valiance in both the Stepstones.
and lately in the Gullet.

346
00:21:56.440 --> 00:21:58.901
You have shown yourself
a leader of men.

347
00:21:58.943 --> 00:22:01.487
I was only doing my duty.
Your Grace.

348
00:22:02.446 --> 00:22:04.073
And Addam
has been my assurance

349
00:22:04.114 --> 00:22:05.366
that the gods favor me.

350
00:22:06.492 --> 00:22:08.452
When my hope had waned.
they sent me you.

351
00:22:09.286 --> 00:22:11.330
It is my great honor
to serve you. Your Grace.

352
00:22:19.129 --> 00:22:20.881
To that end. my queen...

353
00:22:22.550 --> 00:22:25.261
I have acknowledged my sons.

354
00:22:25.302 --> 00:22:26.929
Mm.

355
00:22:26.971 --> 00:22:30.474
And more than that.
I would name Alyn my heir.

356
00:22:35.521 --> 00:22:38.482
I ask that you legitimize them.

357
00:22:39.817 --> 00:22:41.986
Let them now be Velaryons.

358
00:22:43.362 --> 00:22:44.572
Lords of the realm.

359
00:22:45.990 --> 00:22:48.117
For without them.

360
00:22:48.158 --> 00:22:49.577
my line is ended...

361
00:22:50.744 --> 00:22:52.162
and my name erased.

362
00:22:59.420 --> 00:23:03.424
It is well that you have
found an heir.

363
00:23:05.009 --> 00:23:07.261
We have both of us
suffered greatly. and I...

364
00:23:08.554 --> 00:23:10.347
I cannot begrudge you
a new way forward.

365
00:23:10.389 --> 00:23:12.892
- but Lord Corlys...
- A word from the throne.

366
00:23:14.351 --> 00:23:16.020
It is simple enough.

367
00:25:05.462 --> 00:25:07.256
Are your nerves steady.
Your Grace?

368
00:25:07.297 --> 00:25:08.966
As steady as they may be.

369
00:25:10.175 --> 00:25:11.760
I have courted
the smallfolk from afar.

370
00:25:11.802 --> 00:25:13.971
but I have not yet come
before them as their queen.

371
00:25:14.013 --> 00:25:15.848
You have been
much anticipated.

372
00:25:16.974 --> 00:25:20.561
Then. there will be
much expected.

373
00:25:21.562 --> 00:25:22.813
And our resources are few.

374
00:25:22.855 --> 00:25:24.732
I do not know
what satisfaction I can give.

375
00:25:26.817 --> 00:25:30.237
For some. it will be enough to
say they have looked on a queen.

376
00:25:32.656 --> 00:25:34.033
Will I bring your jewels?

377
00:25:36.827 --> 00:25:39.329
I will wear
no needless ornament.

378
00:25:39.371 --> 00:25:42.541
I must show strength.
readiness.

379
00:25:42.583 --> 00:25:44.168
But the sword perhaps.

380
00:25:45.002 --> 00:25:47.629
Might that not contradict
what you wish to convey

381
00:25:47.671 --> 00:25:49.339
to petitioners in need?

382
00:25:51.050 --> 00:25:52.885
Fair point.

383
00:25:52.926 --> 00:25:53.969
Still.

384
00:25:56.096 --> 00:25:59.016
A chain. I think.
For gravity.

385
00:25:59.892 --> 00:26:01.018
One of these.

386
00:26:02.186 --> 00:26:03.187
Fuck.

387
00:26:03.228 --> 00:26:04.229
Your Grace?

388
00:26:05.230 --> 00:26:06.440
I'm bleeding.

389
00:26:07.524 --> 00:26:08.734
- You're sure?
- Yes.

390
00:26:08.776 --> 00:26:11.361
Fuck!

391
00:26:12.237 --> 00:26:13.739
Of course.

392
00:26:13.781 --> 00:26:15.365
I'll fetch some cloths.

393
00:26:16.450 --> 00:26:19.244
Rhaenyra Targaryen.
First of Her Name.

394
00:26:19.286 --> 00:26:23.082
Queen of the Andals.
the Rhoynar. and the First Men.

395
00:26:23.123 --> 00:26:26.794
Lady of the Seven Kingdoms.
and Protector of the Realm.

396
00:26:27.920 --> 00:26:30.172
Your Grace. I am a weaver

397
00:26:30.214 --> 00:26:32.091
and my trade is in wool.

398
00:26:32.925 --> 00:26:35.219
We have a great shortage
now in fleece.

399
00:26:35.260 --> 00:26:39.014
and such sheep as there are
have been taken by dragons.

400
00:26:41.308 --> 00:26:43.518
Might not the fleece
be harvested

401
00:26:43.519 --> 00:26:46.188
before the animal is consumed?
That seems easy enough.

402
00:26:46.230 --> 00:26:48.524
It would be a help. surely.

403
00:26:48.565 --> 00:26:51.193
but there are many
in our guild.

404
00:26:51.235 --> 00:26:54.655
To restore our resources.
we would need an investment.

405
00:26:55.572 --> 00:26:57.574
Five hundred golden dragons.

406
00:26:59.326 --> 00:27:01.662
With regards
to the sheep. my queen...

407
00:27:02.913 --> 00:27:05.415
such an outcome does nothing
to supply us with meat.

408
00:27:06.333 --> 00:27:09.378
- We butchers have no trade.
- Is there no game to be had?

409
00:27:09.419 --> 00:27:11.296
Oh. not for miles.

410
00:27:11.338 --> 00:27:14.216
And all the hunters
have been taken for archers.

411
00:27:14.258 --> 00:27:16.260
If we could but receive
some expenditure

412
00:27:16.301 --> 00:27:18.595
- from the crown...
- Might... might we consider the Kingswood?

413
00:27:21.056 --> 00:27:23.809
That would be a bold gesture.
Your Grace.

414
00:27:23.851 --> 00:27:26.436
One that would have offended
your royal forebears.

415
00:27:27.855 --> 00:27:30.149
Neither stags nor boars.

416
00:27:30.190 --> 00:27:32.651
but. uh. rabbits. perhaps.

417
00:27:32.693 --> 00:27:35.863
It bears discussion
in a forum other than this one.

418
00:27:36.780 --> 00:27:38.282
Let the next petitioner come.

419
00:27:39.158 --> 00:27:41.577
I am Sylvi. Your Grace.

420
00:27:41.618 --> 00:27:43.287
I was privileged
to be of assistance

421
00:27:43.328 --> 00:27:46.707
to the Lady Mysaria in her
campaign against the usurper.

422
00:27:47.583 --> 00:27:51.086
I thank you. a-and all here
who kept the faith.

423
00:27:51.128 --> 00:27:53.463
My appeal is not for coin...

424
00:27:54.464 --> 00:27:57.134
but for justice
for what the commonfolk

425
00:27:57.176 --> 00:27:58.927
have suffered these long months.

426
00:28:01.972 --> 00:28:04.850
The blockade is lifted.
It will not be long now

427
00:28:04.892 --> 00:28:06.810
- before trade routes are reestablished...
- It was not only the blockade

428
00:28:06.852 --> 00:28:09.354
that drove us to want.
Your Grace.

429
00:28:11.231 --> 00:28:14.651
It was the rich.
The noble lords.

430
00:28:14.693 --> 00:28:17.279
They bought up everything
they could for their storehouses

431
00:28:17.321 --> 00:28:19.114
and left the poorer folk
with nothing.

432
00:28:19.156 --> 00:28:21.283
Is this true?

433
00:28:21.325 --> 00:28:24.328
I am no innocent. my queen.

434
00:28:24.369 --> 00:28:26.205
It is the way of the world.

435
00:28:26.246 --> 00:28:28.207
But when the highborn
take even what little remains

436
00:28:28.248 --> 00:28:31.668
and put it aside.
while the lowborn starve...

437
00:28:33.670 --> 00:28:36.340
then that is a matter
I would put before my queen...

438
00:28:37.758 --> 00:28:42.012
who came to power
as a champion of her people.

439
00:28:53.649 --> 00:28:55.984
It is a dangerous element
that seeks to blame the wealthy

440
00:28:56.026 --> 00:28:57.694
for the city's woes.

441
00:28:57.736 --> 00:29:00.364
In a war. all suffer.

442
00:29:00.405 --> 00:29:03.158
- Some more than others.
- That has ever been so.

443
00:29:03.200 --> 00:29:05.410
And yet. in times like these.
it is a cudgel

444
00:29:05.452 --> 00:29:09.331
in irresponsible hands used to
strike up unrest and rebellion.

445
00:29:09.373 --> 00:29:10.916
- Do the commonfolk...
- For the cramps.

446
00:29:10.958 --> 00:29:12.542
...not deserve the providence

447
00:29:12.584 --> 00:29:14.211
and protection
of their ruler?

448
00:29:14.253 --> 00:29:16.171
It is a covenant broken

449
00:29:16.213 --> 00:29:18.173
- at our peril.
- Eh.

450
00:29:18.215 --> 00:29:19.675
They look to us
for order and security.

451
00:29:19.716 --> 00:29:21.343
They look to us for meat

452
00:29:21.385 --> 00:29:23.011
and fuel for their fires.

453
00:29:23.053 --> 00:29:25.180
And who is us.
in your telling?

454
00:29:25.222 --> 00:29:28.183
I have earned
my seat at this table.

455
00:29:28.225 --> 00:29:30.102
though I was not born to it.

456
00:29:30.143 --> 00:29:33.230
I will leave others to judge
which path most has merit.

457
00:29:33.272 --> 00:29:35.357
Has Baela returned?

458
00:29:35.399 --> 00:29:37.109
What news of Vhagar
and Sheepstealer?

459
00:29:37.150 --> 00:29:38.986
The only dragon
she saw was Sunfyre.

460
00:29:40.070 --> 00:29:41.530
Long dead and decaying.

461
00:29:41.571 --> 00:29:43.198
She flies again this evening.

462
00:29:43.240 --> 00:29:44.950
Let us send Addam with her.

463
00:29:46.243 --> 00:29:47.744
They cannot hide for long.

464
00:29:50.163 --> 00:29:51.456
You will have justice.

465
00:29:51.498 --> 00:29:53.083
I will never have justice.

466
00:29:54.459 --> 00:29:58.088
But what crumbs of it may be snatched.
I will devour.

467
00:30:00.632 --> 00:30:02.050
In the meantime. Your Grace.

468
00:30:02.092 --> 00:30:03.969
I urge you. turn your mind
to the issue before us...

469
00:30:04.011 --> 00:30:05.470
There is no issue.
There are bellyachers

470
00:30:05.512 --> 00:30:07.973
bleating their dissatisfaction
at the order of things.

471
00:30:08.015 --> 00:30:09.099
Lord Corlys.

472
00:30:11.101 --> 00:30:12.436
I defer to the queen.

473
00:30:13.687 --> 00:30:14.938
Useless.

474
00:30:16.023 --> 00:30:17.941
What would your father do?

475
00:30:24.698 --> 00:30:26.783
A banquet. I think.

476
00:30:34.958 --> 00:30:36.960
Great day for the three of you.

477
00:30:37.002 --> 00:30:39.087
We are much honored.
Your Grace.

478
00:30:39.129 --> 00:30:41.923
Ulf. how will you
style yourself?

479
00:30:41.965 --> 00:30:43.300
Oh. uh...

480
00:30:44.843 --> 00:30:46.303
Targaryen. Your Grace.

481
00:30:46.345 --> 00:30:47.804
Oh. absolutely not.

482
00:30:50.515 --> 00:30:52.351
Then. I have no style.

483
00:30:52.392 --> 00:30:54.353
So fashion one.

484
00:30:57.731 --> 00:30:58.982
White. then?

485
00:31:02.861 --> 00:31:04.738
Good. Um. and you?

486
00:31:06.907 --> 00:31:09.368
I'm a blacksmith by trade.
Your Grace.

487
00:31:10.660 --> 00:31:11.828
I go by Hammer.

488
00:31:14.164 --> 00:31:15.540
Hugh the Hammer.

489
00:31:16.375 --> 00:31:17.834
Ulf the White.

490
00:31:24.007 --> 00:31:25.675
And Addam of Hull.

491
00:31:35.102 --> 00:31:36.353
Kneel.

492
00:31:47.030 --> 00:31:50.617
In the name of the Warrior.
I charge you to be brave.

493
00:31:57.374 --> 00:32:00.419
In the name of the Father.
I charge you to be just.

494
00:32:04.589 --> 00:32:06.883
In the name of the Mother.
I charge you

495
00:32:06.925 --> 00:32:08.802
to defend the young
and the innocent.

496
00:32:16.309 --> 00:32:19.229
- Is that it?
- Ser Ulf.

497
00:32:21.565 --> 00:32:24.276
Ser Hugh.
Ser Addam.

498
00:32:24.317 --> 00:32:26.694
Knights in
your queen's service.

499
00:32:26.695 --> 00:32:29.906
Will you swear fealty to
your ruler and her cause?

500
00:32:29.948 --> 00:32:33.535
To be servants and agents of the crown
for all of your days?

501
00:32:33.577 --> 00:32:35.245
I swear it. Your Grace.

502
00:32:36.580 --> 00:32:38.373
As do I.

503
00:32:38.415 --> 00:32:40.207
Until death.

504
00:32:40.208 --> 00:32:42.085
Ser Luthor.
I wish to consult with you

505
00:32:42.127 --> 00:32:44.379
about a notion I have.

506
00:32:44.421 --> 00:32:47.299
A dinner for various nobles
whom you may identify...

507
00:32:47.340 --> 00:32:48.592
Your Grace.

508
00:32:51.511 --> 00:32:55.265
I was wondering what sort
of living I may expect.

509
00:32:55.307 --> 00:32:57.392
now that we're in
King's Landing.

510
00:32:57.434 --> 00:33:00.228
Uh... uh. yes. of course.

511
00:33:00.270 --> 00:33:03.732
Uh. I did promise to provide
for you and your wife.

512
00:33:03.773 --> 00:33:06.234
She's gone.
I went into the city to find her.

513
00:33:06.276 --> 00:33:08.487
only to hear that she's gone to live
with her brother in Tumbleton.

514
00:33:08.528 --> 00:33:10.405
There was nothing for her here.

515
00:33:10.447 --> 00:33:13.074
Send to her.
and. uh. we will set aside

516
00:33:13.116 --> 00:33:15.285
a house for you
on Visenya's Hill.

517
00:33:15.327 --> 00:33:18.580
And when might that be.
Your Grace?

518
00:33:18.622 --> 00:33:20.248
As soon as I am able.

519
00:33:20.290 --> 00:33:23.168
I have no small council
at present.

520
00:33:24.544 --> 00:33:26.086
Nor a Queensguard to serve me.

521
00:33:26.087 --> 00:33:29.799
I am awash in dilemmas
and deficiencies.

522
00:33:29.841 --> 00:33:31.635
Let me find my footing.

523
00:33:31.676 --> 00:33:33.720
and I will attend
to your requests.

524
00:33:41.144 --> 00:33:43.313
The queen dowager.
Your Grace.

525
00:33:46.900 --> 00:33:48.568
Uh. very well.

526
00:33:59.162 --> 00:34:00.330
With thanks.

527
00:34:03.083 --> 00:34:04.167
Your Grace.

528
00:34:05.544 --> 00:34:07.546
I'm sorry I was sharp
when we spoke.

529
00:34:10.507 --> 00:34:12.592
I have a small request only.

530
00:34:14.427 --> 00:34:16.179
We'll hear it.

531
00:34:17.514 --> 00:34:21.101
Only that my father's remains
be sent to Oldtown...

532
00:34:22.394 --> 00:34:24.187
where they may lie
beside my mother's.

533
00:34:33.196 --> 00:34:34.656
As you say.

534
00:34:34.698 --> 00:34:35.907
Thank you.

535
00:34:47.877 --> 00:34:50.714
It is odd
to be here with you.

536
00:34:52.757 --> 00:34:53.758
Alicent.

537
00:35:03.101 --> 00:35:05.270
You ruled this realm
in all but name

538
00:35:05.312 --> 00:35:06.771
while my father lay ill.

539
00:35:08.565 --> 00:35:09.649
I did.

540
00:35:14.571 --> 00:35:15.739
I heard...

541
00:35:16.740 --> 00:35:18.241
petitions today.

542
00:35:21.786 --> 00:35:23.413
There are many of them.

543
00:35:24.748 --> 00:35:26.625
And their needs
are many more. It's a...

544
00:35:27.792 --> 00:35:29.753
heavy weight.

545
00:35:33.673 --> 00:35:35.258
How did you bear it?

546
00:35:38.595 --> 00:35:39.638
In truth?

547
00:35:44.809 --> 00:35:48.855
You may not rule
and remain yourself.

548
00:35:52.359 --> 00:35:53.943
There are choices to be made

549
00:35:53.985 --> 00:35:56.655
and you may. on occasion.

550
00:35:56.696 --> 00:35:59.449
have to turn your face away
while people suffer and die.

551
00:36:01.951 --> 00:36:03.787
There is in you
a door that must shut.

552
00:36:05.288 --> 00:36:07.332
You will do things

553
00:36:07.374 --> 00:36:10.001
that your heart
would have recoiled from

554
00:36:10.043 --> 00:36:12.003
before you came to the throne.

555
00:36:12.879 --> 00:36:15.632
I acknowledge the struggle.

556
00:36:15.674 --> 00:36:17.467
But I dispute that I must
become what I am not.

557
00:36:20.637 --> 00:36:21.971
Time will tell.

558
00:36:24.349 --> 00:36:25.975
My father remained himself.

559
00:36:26.017 --> 00:36:28.937
Your father lived in
a world of his own construction.

560
00:36:28.978 --> 00:36:30.980
You and I have never
set foot there.

561
00:36:35.402 --> 00:36:36.695
Be welcome.

562
00:36:39.823 --> 00:36:42.200
You have all heard. I'm sure.

563
00:36:42.242 --> 00:36:45.328
that our ascension is proclaimed
throughout the realm.

564
00:36:45.370 --> 00:36:47.872
Already the Hightowers
have bent the knee before me.

565
00:36:47.914 --> 00:36:52.127
and. likewise. those in this room
have pledged their loyalty.

566
00:36:54.212 --> 00:36:56.296
Later than I would have liked.

567
00:36:56.297 --> 00:36:59.718
But I come before you
as a conciliator.

568
00:37:11.521 --> 00:37:14.649
It is our privilege.
Your Grace.

569
00:37:14.691 --> 00:37:17.277
to attend you here at last.

570
00:37:18.278 --> 00:37:21.655
I avow.
which all here know.

571
00:37:21.656 --> 00:37:25.034
that I mistrusted the Hightower claim
from the beginning.

572
00:37:26.536 --> 00:37:28.037
I'm sure that's true.

573
00:37:28.079 --> 00:37:30.998
even if I heard no tale of you
rising up to protest it.

574
00:37:32.792 --> 00:37:35.670
Ah.
I see our feast is served.

575
00:38:03.573 --> 00:38:04.741
What is this?

576
00:38:06.701 --> 00:38:09.454
This is what the commonfolk
of my city ate.

577
00:38:09.496 --> 00:38:12.415
this and worse. while you
and those like you

578
00:38:12.457 --> 00:38:14.250
hid provisions away
in your storehouses.

579
00:38:15.627 --> 00:38:17.921
Your Grace. we were afraid.

580
00:38:17.962 --> 00:38:20.632
Will you have had us starve
and our families with us?

581
00:38:20.673 --> 00:38:21.966
I would have no one starve.

582
00:38:22.008 --> 00:38:24.135
I would have those with much

583
00:38:24.177 --> 00:38:27.639
exercise stewardship
and tend to those with little.

584
00:38:27.680 --> 00:38:29.808
as a shepherd
tends to their sheep.

585
00:38:29.849 --> 00:38:32.559
The poor. like rats. overrun the city.

586
00:38:32.560 --> 00:38:34.938
They thieve and fight
for every crumb.

587
00:38:34.979 --> 00:38:37.899
And would you not do the same
if your children were hungry?

588
00:38:37.941 --> 00:38:39.400
No. I would not.

589
00:38:39.442 --> 00:38:40.819
Hm. admirable restraint.

590
00:38:40.860 --> 00:38:43.321
You would lie genteel
in your grave.

591
00:38:45.031 --> 00:38:47.659
As you sit here.
my Gold Cloaks

592
00:38:47.700 --> 00:38:49.285
are entering
each of your houses.

593
00:38:49.327 --> 00:38:51.996
They are searching your storerooms

594
00:38:52.038 --> 00:38:53.914
for all that you hoarded away.

595
00:38:53.915 --> 00:38:55.582
And they will bring
what they find back to me

596
00:38:55.583 --> 00:38:58.461
for distribution to those
in my city who need it.

597
00:38:58.503 --> 00:39:01.172
- This is unconscionable.
- We're being robbed!

598
00:39:01.214 --> 00:39:03.591
What the crown
demands of you

599
00:39:03.633 --> 00:39:05.260
is not plunder. but a duty.

600
00:39:05.301 --> 00:39:07.136
And tonight.
will serve as a lesson

601
00:39:07.178 --> 00:39:10.431
in what I will require of you
now and henceforth.

602
00:39:10.473 --> 00:39:11.516
Good evening.

603
00:39:24.070 --> 00:39:25.321
Your Grace.

604
00:39:29.659 --> 00:39:31.452
House Manderly. is it?

605
00:39:31.494 --> 00:39:33.496
Ser Torrhen Manderly.
Your Grace.

606
00:39:33.538 --> 00:39:34.873
your humble servant.

607
00:39:35.915 --> 00:39:38.751
Is it humility that causes you
to smile so. Ser Torrhen?

608
00:39:39.752 --> 00:39:41.713
It is admiration
only for a hand well played.

609
00:39:43.006 --> 00:39:45.550
My Gold Cloaks will be visitors
to your household as well.

610
00:39:45.592 --> 00:39:48.261
And no doubt I am
as deserving as any here.

611
00:39:49.095 --> 00:39:51.848
It is a bold move.
and the smallfolk will cheer it.

612
00:39:51.890 --> 00:39:54.225
It may even make them forget
that it was your blockade

613
00:39:54.267 --> 00:39:56.185
that made bread scarce
in the first place.

614
00:39:59.522 --> 00:40:01.232
Well. rest assured.
Ser Torrhen...

615
00:40:02.358 --> 00:40:03.735
my memory is long.

616
00:40:06.237 --> 00:40:08.156
They'll resent you for this.

617
00:40:08.197 --> 00:40:11.326
They are merchants
and minor nobles.

618
00:40:11.367 --> 00:40:12.827
They've been in error
and they know it.

619
00:40:12.869 --> 00:40:14.329
I do admit.
I find it amusing.

620
00:40:14.370 --> 00:40:16.205
It will help
a certain number of people

621
00:40:16.247 --> 00:40:17.540
for a certain number of weeks

622
00:40:17.582 --> 00:40:19.083
and do nothing
for the rest of them.

623
00:40:19.125 --> 00:40:21.753
- It is a gesture only.
- Yes. and gestures matter.

624
00:40:21.794 --> 00:40:26.341
But you say rightly that
this is not a lasting solution.

625
00:40:26.382 --> 00:40:27.884
For that.
I will need you to fly.

626
00:40:29.052 --> 00:40:30.511
Go to the Vale.

627
00:40:30.553 --> 00:40:33.014
Lady Jeyne never sent
the swords she promised.

628
00:40:33.056 --> 00:40:34.557
She may pay her debt in coin.

629
00:40:36.142 --> 00:40:37.810
This is an errand
I will relish.

630
00:40:38.853 --> 00:40:41.356
The other great houses
I will summon here.

631
00:40:41.397 --> 00:40:42.941
In the meantime.
return with gold

632
00:40:42.982 --> 00:40:45.735
or pledges of gold. else we are hobbled
before we begin.

633
00:40:50.907 --> 00:40:53.242
You have come so far.

634
00:40:53.284 --> 00:40:55.453
and yet you still don't know
who you are.

635
00:40:56.579 --> 00:40:58.538
If I fail to administer
my city.

636
00:40:58.539 --> 00:41:00.291
how will I be trusted
to govern a realm?

637
00:41:00.333 --> 00:41:02.043
Aegon the Conqueror
had three dragons.

638
00:41:02.085 --> 00:41:05.212
You now have six.
It is a power beyond imagining.

639
00:41:05.213 --> 00:41:07.757
Why scrabble here for gold
when the world lies before us?

640
00:41:07.799 --> 00:41:09.759
Dorne could be ours.

641
00:41:10.802 --> 00:41:14.055
And then Essos
and the Free Cities.

642
00:41:14.097 --> 00:41:15.682
Yi Ti and its riches.

643
00:41:19.686 --> 00:41:21.896
They say there is a city
at the edge of the world

644
00:41:21.938 --> 00:41:23.439
where men have wings.

645
00:41:26.943 --> 00:41:29.904
I remember wishing to go there
to see them for myself.

646
00:41:29.946 --> 00:41:32.323
Those men will serve us.
They will serve you.

647
00:41:35.326 --> 00:41:37.620
You will have
an empire unassailable.

648
00:41:39.330 --> 00:41:41.624
And our children will rule it
forever and a day.

649
00:41:41.666 --> 00:41:43.751
You style us commandeers
and marauders

650
00:41:43.793 --> 00:41:45.336
like the pirates
that plague us.

651
00:41:45.378 --> 00:41:47.171
I style us gods. Rhaenyra.

652
00:41:51.384 --> 00:41:53.177
As we were always meant to be.

653
00:42:26.502 --> 00:42:28.004
And I've made my peace
with him.

654
00:42:29.338 --> 00:42:30.923
But he renounced his dragon.

655
00:42:55.948 --> 00:42:57.200
Your Grace.

656
00:43:01.120 --> 00:43:02.705
You still have to kill Daeron.

657
00:43:54.632 --> 00:43:56.342
You are tired today.

658
00:43:57.426 --> 00:43:58.928
I cannot sleep in that bed.

659
00:43:58.970 --> 00:44:01.347
Mm. a new mattress. perhaps.

660
00:44:02.598 --> 00:44:04.642
Perhaps.

661
00:44:07.019 --> 00:44:09.313
You have buried your grief.

662
00:44:09.355 --> 00:44:11.440
I feel no grief.
I feel nothing.

663
00:44:14.610 --> 00:44:17.280
Well. no.
There is rage.

664
00:44:20.283 --> 00:44:22.285
A rage that billows
beyond my grasp.

665
00:44:23.161 --> 00:44:24.453
I have known such rage.

666
00:44:30.626 --> 00:44:33.171
I will look on those
who killed my sons. Mysaria.

667
00:44:35.173 --> 00:44:36.174
I will.

668
00:44:54.692 --> 00:44:57.278
Let the Septon deny you.

669
00:44:57.320 --> 00:44:58.988
This will be your anointing.

670
00:45:08.581 --> 00:45:11.083
Rhaenyra! Rhaenyra!

671
00:45:14.253 --> 00:45:17.423
I have been away.
uh. too long.

672
00:45:18.841 --> 00:45:22.970
But we are at last reunited.

673
00:45:31.520 --> 00:45:33.648
The usurpers are vanquished.

674
00:45:33.689 --> 00:45:35.733
and I have taken
my rightful throne...

675
00:45:37.276 --> 00:45:40.780
...from which I shall
rule judiciously...

676
00:45:41.781 --> 00:45:45.243
with strength.
but also mercy...

677
00:45:46.369 --> 00:45:49.163
as befits a true queen.

678
00:45:53.709 --> 00:45:57.546
In token of which
I bring you gifts for your relief.

679
00:46:01.300 --> 00:46:05.763
And in honor of my father
who came before me.

680
00:46:08.724 --> 00:46:10.184
Gods be with you.

681
00:46:37.962 --> 00:46:39.088
Your Grace.

682
00:46:41.090 --> 00:46:43.092
- A word.
- Walk with me.

683
00:46:44.010 --> 00:46:45.553
You made Addam a knight.

684
00:46:45.594 --> 00:46:49.056
but it seems you styled him
Hull rather than Velaryon.

685
00:46:49.098 --> 00:46:51.892
We had agreed. I thought.
that he and Alyn

686
00:46:51.934 --> 00:46:53.394
would be legitimized.

687
00:46:53.436 --> 00:46:55.771
Now. if it is a matter
of ceremony or...

688
00:46:56.856 --> 00:46:59.442
Um. I'm sorry. Corlys.

689
00:46:59.483 --> 00:47:02.445
but in this moment
I cannot do as you ask.

690
00:47:05.364 --> 00:47:08.784
I have given all I had.

691
00:47:08.826 --> 00:47:11.203
everything. in service to you.

692
00:47:12.455 --> 00:47:14.165
My castle lies in ashes.

693
00:47:14.206 --> 00:47:16.625
and I have asked no favor
in return but this.

694
00:47:18.377 --> 00:47:20.296
You know very well the rumors

695
00:47:20.338 --> 00:47:22.381
that have dogged my sons
from the first.

696
00:47:23.674 --> 00:47:25.843
My reign has just begun.

697
00:47:25.885 --> 00:47:29.347
I cannot in this moment
be seen to raise up those...

698
00:47:31.182 --> 00:47:33.225
born outside
of noble troth. I...

699
00:47:35.144 --> 00:47:37.146
And so you will
insult my house...

700
00:47:38.481 --> 00:47:40.983
so that you may be seen
to be something you are not.

701
00:47:42.151 --> 00:47:43.778
I have Joffrey to think of.

702
00:47:43.819 --> 00:47:45.946
I was staunch in my defense

703
00:47:45.988 --> 00:47:48.783
when your own troth
was... doubted.

704
00:47:48.824 --> 00:47:51.285
Yes. and I thank you for this.

705
00:47:51.327 --> 00:47:52.745
among many other things.

706
00:47:53.746 --> 00:47:55.706
But all eyes look to me now.

707
00:47:56.957 --> 00:48:00.669
Perhaps one day when there
is not so much scrutiny...

708
00:48:00.711 --> 00:48:02.213
You are ashamed.

709
00:48:04.131 --> 00:48:05.716
Well...

710
00:48:05.758 --> 00:48:08.511
- It is a matter of legitimacy.
- Your son Joffrey...

711
00:48:09.887 --> 00:48:11.263
is a bastard.

712
00:48:13.224 --> 00:48:14.892
Your son. Lucerys.

713
00:48:14.934 --> 00:48:17.353
whom I accepted
as my heir...

714
00:48:18.896 --> 00:48:20.731
- was a bastard.
- Lord Corlys.

715
00:48:20.773 --> 00:48:24.443
Your son Jacaerys
lived and died a bastard!

716
00:48:28.030 --> 00:48:30.491
Say aloud to me
the reason your children

717
00:48:30.533 --> 00:48:32.410
deserve what mine are denied.

718
00:48:39.083 --> 00:48:41.877
Helaena has gone
to the Godswood. with thanks.

719
00:48:41.919 --> 00:48:44.422
I have your son Daeron here

720
00:48:44.463 --> 00:48:46.048
within these walls.

721
00:48:49.135 --> 00:48:50.845
Here since when?

722
00:48:50.886 --> 00:48:52.763
Uh. he was delivered to me
two days ago

723
00:48:52.805 --> 00:48:57.309
as part of the terms under
which your cousin surrendered.

724
00:49:05.317 --> 00:49:06.569
And what do you...

725
00:49:07.570 --> 00:49:09.071
what do you plan
to do with him?

726
00:49:09.905 --> 00:49:11.824
By rights. I should
have his head. but...

727
00:49:12.825 --> 00:49:15.411
he had no part
in his brothers' treachery.

728
00:49:16.745 --> 00:49:19.706
He did only what was expected
of him by his elders.

729
00:49:19.707 --> 00:49:23.919
Therefore. I will send him
north to the Wall.

730
00:49:27.465 --> 00:49:29.884
He will take the Black
and he will not return.

731
00:49:29.925 --> 00:49:31.302
but he will keep his life.

732
00:49:34.930 --> 00:49:36.265
Do you wish me
to thank you?

733
00:49:37.766 --> 00:49:39.768
I see you have been merciful.

734
00:49:41.604 --> 00:49:43.647
And yet I grieve
for what could have been.

735
00:49:46.817 --> 00:49:49.236
He was... he was sent
to ward as an infant.

736
00:49:49.278 --> 00:49:50.946
I've seen him once
in the last five years.

737
00:49:50.988 --> 00:49:52.781
I hardly know the boy.

738
00:49:52.823 --> 00:49:54.116
And yet...

739
00:49:56.952 --> 00:50:00.122
From all accounts.
he has borne his lot very bravely.

740
00:50:04.293 --> 00:50:05.711
I wish to see him.

741
00:50:07.129 --> 00:50:09.757
You will join
the Night's Watch

742
00:50:09.798 --> 00:50:11.634
and serve out your days there.

743
00:50:13.135 --> 00:50:15.137
It's a hard road.
but there is honor in it.

744
00:50:25.439 --> 00:50:27.775
I see that nothing moves you.
It's a pity.

745
00:50:27.816 --> 00:50:29.068
Your mother is here.

746
00:50:30.819 --> 00:50:33.989
I would counsel you
to unguard yourself.

747
00:50:34.823 --> 00:50:37.201
One time at least. before you take
your long journey.

748
00:50:37.243 --> 00:50:38.494
The queen dowager. ser.

749
00:50:46.544 --> 00:50:49.004
Here she is.
Look at her.

750
00:51:13.571 --> 00:51:15.030
You don't know this boy.

751
00:51:17.866 --> 00:51:19.285
He is not Daeron.

752
00:51:31.630 --> 00:51:33.674
Who are you then?

753
00:51:33.716 --> 00:51:35.175
Speak!

754
00:51:35.217 --> 00:51:37.094
He compelled me.

755
00:51:37.136 --> 00:51:39.179
- I begged him.
- Who compelled you?

756
00:51:39.221 --> 00:51:40.723
Lord Ormund Hightower.

757
00:51:43.058 --> 00:51:44.852
He blenched my hair.

758
00:51:44.893 --> 00:51:47.062
told me I must play
the part of the prince.

759
00:51:47.938 --> 00:51:49.773
Even if she burned me
with dragons.

760
00:51:50.774 --> 00:51:53.360
I must stay silent.

761
00:51:53.402 --> 00:51:55.571
or he would have
my mother hanged.

762
00:51:56.905 --> 00:51:58.240
My real mother.

763
00:52:00.409 --> 00:52:02.911
She isn't a queen.
Your Grace.

764
00:52:02.953 --> 00:52:06.915
She's only a lady.
and our people are merchants.

765
00:52:06.957 --> 00:52:08.167
Ormund...

766
00:52:09.251 --> 00:52:10.502
has deceived me.

767
00:52:12.588 --> 00:52:14.590
Your real son.
he keeps with him. no doubt.

768
00:52:16.175 --> 00:52:18.469
Did he think
I would not discover it?

769
00:52:41.533 --> 00:52:43.118
What game does he play?

770
00:52:46.622 --> 00:52:47.665
Your Grace.

771
00:52:48.499 --> 00:52:50.793
I am sent to tell you our work here
is all but complete.

772
00:52:50.834 --> 00:52:53.212
The Hightower colors have been
removed throughout these walls.

773
00:52:54.505 --> 00:52:55.881
Burn all of it.

774
00:52:59.718 --> 00:53:00.803
Your Grace.

775
00:53:00.844 --> 00:53:02.471
There's a dragonkeeper
at the gate.

776
00:53:07.142 --> 00:53:08.310
What is it?

777
00:53:20.572 --> 00:53:22.074
- What?
- Yeah.

